1
00:00:15,930 --> 00:00:19,270
{\i1}From when I was little
I had a question in my mind.{\i0}

3
00:00:23,900 --> 00:00:29,860
{\i1}I heard that "I think therefore I am"
are the words of an ancient philosopher.{\i0}

4
00:00:29,860 --> 00:00:32,820
{\i1}But I didn't think.
I thought about someone else.{\i0}

5
00:00:33,660 --> 00:00:36,530
{\i1}That perhaps the person over there
is myself as well...{\i0}

6
00:00:55,550 --> 00:00:59,140
Episode 1
"I think about others"

7
00:00:56,390 --> 00:01:00,720
{\i1}"Think about others."
When I did that I had turned into someone else.{\i0}

8
00:01:03,060 --> 00:01:07,980
{\i1}But no more than five seconds.
After that I immediately returned to my own self.{\i0}

9
00:01:07,980 --> 00:01:11,780
{\i1}Furthermore for the duration
my body completely loses consciousness.{\i0}

10
00:01:12,530 --> 00:01:15,070
{\i1}Often I would find myself 
injured in some way.{\i0}

11
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:18,910
{\i1}Furthermore I can only possess someone
that is within my line of sight.{\i0}

12
00:01:18,910 --> 00:01:21,290
{\i1}So I couldn't use it for lewd things.{\i0}

13
00:01:21,580 --> 00:01:24,210
{\i1}At most it was for possessing someone
that angry me off{\i0}

14
00:01:24,210 --> 00:01:26,790
{\i1}only to pick a fight with a stranger
then return to myself.{\i0}

15
00:01:26,790 --> 00:01:30,420
{\i1}That kind of retaliation was 
all I could use this for.{\i0}

16
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:41,970
You! What do you 
think you just did huh?

17
00:01:43,020 --> 00:01:48,650
{\i1}But finally I came up with an idea
that can take full advantage of this special ability.{\i0}

18
00:01:49,020 --> 00:01:51,900


19
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:52,480
Five minutes before time.

20
00:01:58,660 --> 00:02:01,790
{\i1}I could possess one smart guy in class
after another memorize the answers{\i0}

21
00:02:01,790 --> 00:02:06,250
{\i1}memorize the answers and fill in my answers
after returning... and I repeat that.{\i0}

22
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:12,000
Year-End Test Standings
1 - Yu Otosaka

23
00:02:18,130 --> 00:02:22,310
{\i1}Of course I'm planning on attending
a very prestigious high school.{\i0}

24
00:02:22,310 --> 00:02:27,310
{\i1}However unlike a normal test I don't know
who is intelligent during an entrance exam...{\i0}

25
00:02:28,310 --> 00:02:31,770
{\i1}Ever since I've snuck into
prestigious cram schools one after another{\i0}

26
00:02:31,770 --> 00:02:34,980
{\i1}pretending to be a student 
of that cram school.{\i0}

27
00:02:36,700 --> 00:02:39,360
{\i1}Which student facing entrance exams
apply to which schools?{\i0}

28
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:41,870
{\i1}And which subjects were they best at?{\i0}

29
00:02:41,870 --> 00:02:43,870
{\i1}I researched all of that very thoroughly.{\i0}

30
00:02:43,870 --> 00:02:45,450
High School
Entrance Exam Venue

31
00:02:44,830 --> 00:02:51,080
{\i1}And so I found one student after another that
was vying to enter the same school as I was.{\i0}

32
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:54,000
{\i1}And successfully got admitted 
to an elite high school.{\i0}

33
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:59,130
Entrance Ceremony

34
00:02:54,380 --> 00:02:57,090
Now a word from the representative
for the new students.

35
00:02:57,090 --> 00:02:59,130
Yu Otosaka please go ahead.

36
00:03:00,050 --> 00:03:00,840
Yes!

37
00:03:01,510 --> 00:03:03,890
So that means he's the top of the class!

38
00:03:03,890 --> 00:03:04,850
And he's good-looking to boot...!

39
00:03:04,850 --> 00:03:08,770
Entrance Ceremony

40
00:03:12,020 --> 00:03:17,070
Today for us new students you have organized
a grand ceremony of this sort

41
00:03:17,070 --> 00:03:19,490
and we are deeply in gratitude for it.

42
00:03:19,490 --> 00:03:21,700
Wrapped in the warm rays 
of the spring sunshine

43
00:03:21,700 --> 00:03:26,040
we are now able to be a part
of the well-established ranks of Hinomori High School.

44
00:03:23,070 --> 00:03:24,030
Hey hey....

45
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:27,160
Isn't he attractive?

46
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:29,370
Yeah he might be your type Mitchon.

47
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:34,380
Huh? What? Yumi doesn't seem
to be against the idea either?

48
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:40,680
We are very grateful for 
this opportunity today.

49
00:03:43,010 --> 00:03:46,010
Previous Term Class Ranking
1 - Yu Otosaka

50
00:03:57,980 --> 00:04:00,740
Sorry for the sudden email:
My name is Sugimoto from Class 1-2.
Will you possibly come to the back
of the school building after school?
I will be waiting for you till the night.

51
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:00,740
{\i1}This again...{\i0}

52
00:04:01,030 --> 00:04:03,110
{\i1}Stuff like this is happening more often.{\i0}

53
00:04:03,110 --> 00:04:05,530
{\i1}Not only am I superior
as the top of the class academically{\i0}

54
00:04:05,530 --> 00:04:07,540
{\i1}I'm one of the more physically attractive.{\i0}

55
00:04:07,540 --> 00:04:10,410
{\i1}It's impossible to not be 
popular among girls like this.{\i0}

56
00:04:10,410 --> 00:04:13,170
{\i1}Sheesh I'll hurry them all on home.{\i0}

57
00:04:13,750 --> 00:04:16,290
I'm sorry for calling you 
over all the way out here!

58
00:04:16,670 --> 00:04:19,380
That's fine. What did you want from me?

59
00:04:20,380 --> 00:04:23,720
Um I'm fine from starting as just friends...

60
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:26,390
But can you think about dating me please?

61
00:04:27,970 --> 00:04:32,060
Well... In order to keep my grades up
at where they are now

62
00:04:32,060 --> 00:04:34,730
I have to shave time to 
sleep to keep studying.

63
00:04:34,730 --> 00:04:39,030
I don't have the luxury
of dealing with other people. So I'm sorry.

64
00:04:40,490 --> 00:04:44,530
{\i1}Of course that's a pack of lies.
I don't study whatsoever.{\i0}

65
00:04:44,990 --> 00:04:50,870
I see I understand.
I'm sorry for calling you out like this so suddenly!

66
00:04:52,620 --> 00:04:57,130
{\i1}There's no way I would choose 
normal girls like you ilk.{\i0}

67
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:59,880
{\i1}The one I'm after...{\i0}

68
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:03,340
So Yumi you missed
the special program from yesterday?!

69
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:06,340
{\i1}Of course is the madonna of this school...{\i0}

70
00:05:07,510 --> 00:05:09,390
{\i1}Yumi Shirayanagi.{\i0}

71
00:05:09,970 --> 00:05:11,930
{\i1}I will...{\i0}

72
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:13,310
{\i1}...make you mine!{\i0}

73
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:16,310
{\i1}I know I will definitely get a chance.{\i0}

74
00:05:16,650 --> 00:05:21,570
{\i1}It all lies in how I use the five seconds
which are the limits of my ability!{\i0}

75
00:05:16,650 --> 00:05:21,570
And so I was texting until 3 o'clock last night
so I overslept... it was so hard for me to get up!

76
00:05:24,280 --> 00:05:25,490
{\i1}That's it!{\i0}

77
00:05:25,740 --> 00:05:26,610
So...

78
00:05:28,950 --> 00:05:30,580
Mitchon what's wrong?

79
00:05:47,140 --> 00:05:48,550
Call the police!

80
00:05:48,550 --> 00:05:50,560
Are you all right?

81
00:05:53,890 --> 00:05:54,850
Oh it looks like he's okay.

82
00:05:54,850 --> 00:05:55,850
I'm so glad...

83
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:59,860
{\i1}That was close but that 
went according to plan...{\i0}

84
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:01,730
Yumi!

85
00:06:01,980 --> 00:06:03,490
Are you all right?

86
00:06:03,490 --> 00:06:05,450
That was a close one.

87
00:06:05,780 --> 00:06:11,910
Yumi you were about to be run over by a truck
when Otosaka from class 1 saved you!

88
00:06:11,910 --> 00:06:13,910
Is that true...?

89
00:06:13,910 --> 00:06:16,540
Yeah. Are you hurt anywhere?

90
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:20,790
Let's go to the nurse's office. Can you walk?

91
00:06:22,460 --> 00:06:23,460
Yes...

92
00:06:27,090 --> 00:06:28,760
Then I'll go home now.

93
00:06:29,340 --> 00:06:31,140
Please wait!

94
00:06:31,140 --> 00:06:32,640
U-Um...

95
00:06:32,640 --> 00:06:38,650
The two of us were about to go eat
our favorite pancakes together...

96
00:06:38,650 --> 00:06:40,560
would you like to come with us?

97
00:06:41,730 --> 00:06:45,650
I'll have to pass.
It's better to keep that among friends right?

98
00:06:45,650 --> 00:06:49,410
But you just saved my life!

99
00:06:49,410 --> 00:06:54,870
I'd like to properly repay that
and I'd like to chat with you a little while longer...

100
00:06:57,160 --> 00:06:59,460
Whoa I have a call. Who is it?

101
00:06:59,460 --> 00:07:02,090
Then I'll go home. Yup yup yup.

102
00:07:02,090 --> 00:07:03,840
Mitchon what's wrong?

103
00:07:04,420 --> 00:07:06,460
My big brother suddenly came back from Kyoto

104
00:07:06,460 --> 00:07:09,840
and he apparently ordered
top-end sushi for the entire family!

105
00:07:09,840 --> 00:07:12,470
So I'm leaving the rest 
to the two of you! Thanks!

106
00:07:12,470 --> 00:07:16,350
{\i1}That was an obvious farce
but a nice assist nonetheless Mitchon!{\i0}

107
00:07:21,020 --> 00:07:22,560
Sorry to make you wait.

108
00:07:26,230 --> 00:07:28,700
Um there's a special way to eat this.

109
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:29,570
Oh?

110
00:07:29,570 --> 00:07:30,740
Please mimic me.

111
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:35,160
If you do this the syrup
gets across to the entire thing.

112
00:07:35,290 --> 00:07:38,750
Then stack them up cut 
them and try a bite of it.

113
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:51,840
Amazing! Just by changing how you eat it
it gets this delicious? I never knew!

114
00:07:54,970 --> 00:07:58,060
No matter how many times I 
eat this it's delicious...

115
00:07:59,020 --> 00:08:01,140
Oh um...

116
00:08:01,140 --> 00:08:04,440
The song they're playing right now
is Haro-haro isn't it?

117
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:05,900
Haro-haro?

118
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:10,650
You don't know of them?
I had thought every boy knew of them very well.

119
00:08:10,650 --> 00:08:13,370
So something like them is popular nowadays?

120
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:17,660
Otosaka can we go home
together from school

121
00:08:17,660 --> 00:08:20,580
or have an occasional meal together
like this again sometime?

122
00:08:21,290 --> 00:08:23,040
Sure I guess.

123
00:08:24,080 --> 00:08:25,290
I'm so glad...

124
00:08:30,470 --> 00:08:32,220
Shall we go home together today as well?
I will be waiting for you near the main gate.

125
00:08:41,850 --> 00:08:44,060
{\i1}Oh I shouldn't do this out loud.{\i0}

126
00:08:44,060 --> 00:08:45,150
{\i1}I guess I'll hurry on over.{\i0}

127
00:08:45,270 --> 00:08:51,490
{\i1}Yu Otosaka from class 1-1 please report immediately
to the student council room. I repeat...{\i0}

128
00:08:51,030 --> 00:08:52,570
What's this?

129
00:08:51,490 --> 00:08:56,240
{\i1}Yu Otosaka from class 1-1 please report immediately
to the student council room.{\i0}

130
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:56,240
-Sorry I will be late.

131
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:57,620
-Sorry I will be late.
-I will be waiting.

132
00:08:58,080 --> 00:08:59,870
I'm Omura the student council president.

133
00:09:00,370 --> 00:09:05,130
What do you want with me? I'm making someone
wait so I'd like you to make it quick.

134
00:09:05,130 --> 00:09:11,920
That is really up to you. This is a copy of your
answer sheet to the aptitude test from the other day.

135
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:13,380
A perfect score... so marvelous.

136
00:09:13,970 --> 00:09:16,550
The same exact test has 
been placed right there.

137
00:09:16,550 --> 00:09:19,680
Right here right now please try
to get a perfect score once again.

138
00:09:19,680 --> 00:09:20,680
Huh?

139
00:09:20,680 --> 00:09:22,520
What meaning is there behind that?

140
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:26,100
There is an accusation
that you may have cheated on the exam.

141
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:30,110
If you can get 90% or above you are innocent.
You will be deemed guilty if your score is any lower.

142
00:09:30,110 --> 00:09:32,610
This is absurd! I will 
excuse myself right now!

143
00:09:32,610 --> 00:09:37,320
Concerning this case we have the authorization
of both the principal and the vice-principal.

144
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:39,870
If you escape now you will apparently
be expelled from the school.

145
00:09:39,870 --> 00:09:42,200
E-Expelled?!

146
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:44,210
Now please begin.

147
00:09:51,420 --> 00:09:54,010
{\i1}Right there lies all of the answers...{\i0}

148
00:09:54,010 --> 00:09:57,220
{\i1}I'll possess him and find out!
That's the only way!{\i0}

149
00:10:02,180 --> 00:10:04,390
{\i1}Making such a fool of me!{\i0}

150
00:10:07,190 --> 00:10:09,190
What in the world has happened?

151
00:10:09,190 --> 00:10:12,940
To me it only seemed like 
you were tearing that up?

152
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:14,110
Got him!

153
00:10:17,570 --> 00:10:21,620
Hello there I'm Tomori the student
council president... of another school though.

154
00:10:22,040 --> 00:10:24,790
So I was recording you for all this time.

155
00:10:24,790 --> 00:10:26,830
Can you take a look at the 
video I just recorded?

156
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:28,880
Please take a note of the time.

157
00:10:28,880 --> 00:10:33,000
You were not looking at him
the moment he ripped the answer sheet.

158
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:35,470
Yet you said he ripped it up.

159
00:10:35,470 --> 00:10:37,090
Isn't that a bit strange?

160
00:10:37,090 --> 00:10:39,010
I'll show you others.

161
00:10:39,890 --> 00:10:43,390
You have a special ability 
to possess other people.

162
00:10:44,310 --> 00:10:47,140
Using that you cheat on every exam.

163
00:10:47,730 --> 00:10:49,400
Isn't that right?

164
00:10:49,810 --> 00:10:52,230
T-That's not true!
It's a sleeping disease!

165
00:10:52,230 --> 00:10:55,360
I suddenly get tremendously sleepy
and can't fight that urge!

166
00:10:55,690 --> 00:11:00,280
You really are a troublesome one.
I'll show you this now. Here.

167
00:11:00,700 --> 00:11:03,200
A copy of your medical exams.

168
00:11:03,990 --> 00:11:06,710
As far as this goes such 
a disease doesn't exist.

169
00:11:07,210 --> 00:11:09,870
Now please solve the problems on the test.

170
00:11:11,630 --> 00:11:14,340
Such a farce! I can't deal with it!

171
00:11:19,930 --> 00:11:24,760
I see... she had foreseen
that it would even end up this way.

172
00:11:24,760 --> 00:11:28,180
Then everything from here on is my job.

173
00:11:32,980 --> 00:11:34,820
Run! Right now!

174
00:11:36,400 --> 00:11:37,780
!

175
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:42,120
Are you all right?

176
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:44,580
Y-Yes... I'm fine.

177
00:12:20,450 --> 00:12:21,400
{\i1}What?{\i0}

178
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:23,700
{\i1}What is going on here?!{\i0}

179
00:13:20,710 --> 00:13:23,550
You... what did you just do?

180
00:13:23,550 --> 00:13:25,050
Teleportation.

181
00:13:25,050 --> 00:13:26,260
Teleportation?

182
00:13:26,510 --> 00:13:30,890
Yes. Just like it sounds I teleport instantly
to move to another location.

183
00:13:30,890 --> 00:13:33,440
But this ability doesn't let me
conveniently stop exactly where I want.

184
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:37,980
Thanks to this ability I don't know
how many times I've been hospitalized...

185
00:13:37,980 --> 00:13:40,150
{\i1}What an incomplete ability!{\i0}

186
00:13:40,440 --> 00:13:43,400
But anyway what are you
going to do with me from now on?!

187
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:46,410
We will have you transfer over to our school.

188
00:13:50,490 --> 00:13:51,490
Transfer?!

189
00:13:51,490 --> 00:13:56,830
Yes. In this world there are many people
who possess special powers not just you.

190
00:13:57,250 --> 00:14:00,800
However those special skills can be considered
an illness caught during adolescence

191
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:02,550
and will disappear in due time.

192
00:14:02,550 --> 00:14:07,340
Until it goes away however please keep commuting
to our school the Hoshinoumi Academy.

193
00:14:07,510 --> 00:14:08,300
Huh?!

194
00:14:08,300 --> 00:14:12,270
I already have gotten permission from those
that have parental authority over you.

195
00:14:12,270 --> 00:14:13,350
Such a story...

196
00:14:13,350 --> 00:14:14,430
...exists.

197
00:14:14,890 --> 00:14:18,270
However... you seem like you'd be popular
from just your looks.

198
00:14:18,270 --> 00:14:22,480
Was there also a need to play the role of a genius
by cheating as much as possible?

199
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:24,320
That's the real question.

200
00:14:24,610 --> 00:14:27,070
Oh but thanks to that
you were able to close the gap

201
00:14:27,070 --> 00:14:29,700
between yourself and the female student
you were targeting.

202
00:14:29,700 --> 00:14:31,200
Damn you!

203
00:14:42,750 --> 00:14:45,590
What... she disappeared?

204
00:14:45,590 --> 00:14:47,590
That is her ability.

205
00:14:48,090 --> 00:14:52,510
It can't be... an ability 
to become invisible?

206
00:14:52,510 --> 00:14:56,940
No. To me it only looked 
like her punching you.

207
00:14:57,310 --> 00:15:00,730
Impossible... I was the only one
that couldn't see her?

208
00:15:00,730 --> 00:15:05,780
Right. Her ability is to hide from
visual recognition from one target.

209
00:15:05,780 --> 00:15:08,570
Every other human can see her as normal.

210
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:11,280
{\i1}Another imperfect ability!{\i0}

211
00:15:11,700 --> 00:15:15,410
By the way you will enter
our student council as well.

212
00:15:15,410 --> 00:15:16,410
Huh?

213
00:15:16,410 --> 00:15:20,580
Your ability is useful
so I'd like you to cooperate with us.

214
00:15:20,580 --> 00:15:21,960
For what?

215
00:15:21,960 --> 00:15:26,090
To threaten those that abuse their powers
for no good just like you.

216
00:15:26,670 --> 00:15:30,010
That is the kind of existence we are.

217
00:15:32,680 --> 00:15:33,970
I'm home.

218
00:15:34,560 --> 00:15:36,930
Welcome back Big Brother Yu!

219
00:15:36,930 --> 00:15:39,600
Wait! Wow! What's wrong with your face?

220
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:43,520
Oh well um... it was an 
incident during gym class...

221
00:15:43,770 --> 00:15:47,820
Oh right there was
an amazing phone call from our uncle.

222
00:15:47,820 --> 00:15:49,320
Ayu heard that she and Big Brother Yu

223
00:15:49,320 --> 00:15:51,820
will transfer into Hoshinoumi Academy's
middle- and high-school

224
00:15:51,820 --> 00:15:55,080
as scholarship students!

225
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:56,660
Is that really true?

226
00:15:57,290 --> 00:15:58,410
{\i1}Are you serious?{\i0}

227
00:15:58,910 --> 00:16:00,210
Well... it's true.

228
00:16:00,210 --> 00:16:03,170
The house budget will benefit from this!

229
00:16:03,170 --> 00:16:07,010
Furthermore the uncle is sending us
lots of tasty food to celebrate!

230
00:16:07,420 --> 00:16:09,920
But that means
you have to transfer schools too.

231
00:16:09,920 --> 00:16:12,590
That means you have to say goodbye
to your friends - is that all right?

232
00:16:12,590 --> 00:16:15,810
Nowadays we can use smartphones to chat
while looking at each other's faces

233
00:16:15,810 --> 00:16:18,140
so it's not going to be all that lonely.

234
00:16:18,140 --> 00:16:21,600
Hoshinoumi Academy
Executive Office

235
00:16:18,890 --> 00:16:20,690
I see...

236
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:24,730
Tonight's dinner is... ta-dah!

237
00:16:24,730 --> 00:16:27,980
Congratulations!

238
00:16:25,020 --> 00:16:27,980
Omelet rice your favorite 
dish Big Brother Yu!

239
00:16:28,610 --> 00:16:33,490
{\i1}This again? I said time and again
that it was only when I was little...{\i0}

240
00:16:33,660 --> 00:16:37,160
Congrats! Now let's eat!

241
00:16:38,790 --> 00:16:40,120
{\i1}So sweet...{\i0}

242
00:16:40,620 --> 00:16:46,460
{\i1}Using pizza sauce as the secret ingredient must
have been fitting for my tongue when I was a child.{\i0}

243
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:48,630
How is it? Is it tasty?

244
00:16:48,630 --> 00:16:50,050
Yeah it's tasty.

245
00:16:50,050 --> 00:16:51,680
Really?

246
00:16:51,680 --> 00:16:55,890
I want to eat Mom's omelet rice
for the first time in a while...

247
00:16:55,890 --> 00:16:59,770
Mom huh? Who cares about someone like that.

248
00:17:00,020 --> 00:17:02,060
Are you still upset?

249
00:17:02,060 --> 00:17:07,020
Of course I am... She got divorced
and selfishly shoved custody over to our uncle.

250
00:17:07,020 --> 00:17:11,360
Ayu doesn't understand too much of it
but would like to see you be forgiving!

251
00:17:11,780 --> 00:17:16,530
We don't have any parents. Our only family
is you and me just the two of us.

252
00:17:16,530 --> 00:17:24,920
I see... but Ayu sometimes thinks...
there was one more family member somewhere...

253
00:17:25,250 --> 00:17:29,750
You and I are the only siblings. Do you see
someone in your dream or something?

254
00:17:29,750 --> 00:17:31,840
You're right.

255
00:17:31,840 --> 00:17:35,180
It's a weird feeling as 
if it was really true.

256
00:17:36,010 --> 00:17:38,010
It's totally a dream.

257
00:17:41,430 --> 00:17:44,440
Hey we're going to be up early tomorrow
because we're moving right?

258
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:46,100
Why don't you get to sleep soon?

259
00:17:46,100 --> 00:17:48,650
Please give me just a tiny 
bit more of your time!

260
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:52,240
You really love stars don't you?

261
00:17:52,820 --> 00:17:56,700
You can see way off into the distance
where people will never reach you know?

262
00:17:56,700 --> 00:18:00,240
Ayu thinks that is an amazing thing!

263
00:18:00,240 --> 00:18:04,870
You know if you keep talking only about
the stars at school you'll end up getting isolated.

264
00:18:04,870 --> 00:18:06,670
Why is that?

265
00:18:06,670 --> 00:18:08,040
Speaking from experience.

266
00:18:08,040 --> 00:18:11,250
In living my life a foundation
is to liven up the conversation

267
00:18:11,250 --> 00:18:14,340
by talking about what was on TV last night
instead of talk about the stars.

268
00:18:14,340 --> 00:18:17,050
Experience? Foundation?

269
00:18:17,050 --> 00:18:19,760
It's okay if you don't 
understand. Go to sleep soon.

270
00:18:20,390 --> 00:18:22,390
Roger that!

271
00:18:41,790 --> 00:18:44,660
This is an amazingly huge room!

272
00:18:44,660 --> 00:18:48,500
Can Ayu really use it all 
alone with Big Brother Yu?

273
00:18:48,830 --> 00:18:50,290
Yeah...

274
00:18:50,290 --> 00:18:54,460
Thank you for your hard work!
I may not be much but allow me to help–

275
00:18:54,460 --> 00:18:57,800
Hey the moving company guys
will do it so you don't have to.

276
00:18:57,800 --> 00:19:01,890
I thought I could be at least
of some assistance however...

277
00:19:01,890 --> 00:19:03,770
Don't take their jobs away from them.

278
00:19:03,770 --> 00:19:07,770
Oh! Such a way of thinking
was something that Ayu didn't have!

279
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:12,270
Back at that time what had happened?

280
00:19:12,440 --> 00:19:15,030
That's something I can't say...

281
00:19:15,030 --> 00:19:19,410
Well... I'm going to transfer
to Hoshinoumi Academy now...

282
00:19:20,160 --> 00:19:24,540
Well um... I'm sorry
for all the things that happened.

283
00:19:25,330 --> 00:19:30,960
{\i1}Until this ability goes away I can't be authorized
to travel to an area with no supervision...{\i0}

284
00:19:31,330 --> 00:19:34,590
Shirayanagi if you could
come see me instead I'd be delighted.

285
00:19:34,590 --> 00:19:40,640
But that is just too far. At the least
can it be once a week and can we alternate?

286
00:19:40,640 --> 00:19:44,930
Well... I'm sorry about that too.
I can't come here anymore on my own.

287
00:19:44,930 --> 00:19:46,640
Why?

288
00:19:46,640 --> 00:19:48,440
I can't say why...

289
00:19:48,850 --> 00:19:52,940
{\i1}I am forced to not mention anything
about this case to others.{\i0}

290
00:19:53,690 --> 00:19:56,610
There's nothing that I can do about it...

291
00:19:56,610 --> 00:20:00,820
I am grateful for what you have done.
That feeling will never waver.

292
00:20:01,110 --> 00:20:04,490
However I am not dating you yet.

293
00:20:04,490 --> 00:20:09,210
So for me to chase you
in a one-sided manner is as if I was a stalker.

294
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:15,130
Of course I do feel bad about that.
However I can't go see you on my own.

295
00:20:16,090 --> 00:20:20,050
I understand. From now on
let us walk our own separate paths.

296
00:20:20,680 --> 00:20:21,430
That means...

297
00:20:21,720 --> 00:20:29,810
I will never forget the feeling I have towards you
for saving my life as long as I live. That is all.

298
00:20:29,810 --> 00:20:31,520
That can't be...

299
00:20:32,100 --> 00:20:36,730
Thank you very much for saving me.
I really do appreciate it.

300
00:20:36,730 --> 00:20:41,030
But this is where I bid you farewell.
I hope you stay well.

301
00:20:44,530 --> 00:20:47,790
I got dumped... me...?

302
00:20:50,830 --> 00:20:55,340
Hello! Excuse me! I've already let myself in!

303
00:20:56,750 --> 00:20:58,340
What is it so suddenly?

304
00:20:58,340 --> 00:21:02,130
It's tough when it's just the two of you right?
I came here to help.

305
00:21:02,130 --> 00:21:06,100
Oh are all of you people
from the same school as Big Brother Yu?

306
00:21:06,550 --> 00:21:12,440
Yes. We are from the student council.
I am Takajo and this is Tomori.

307
00:21:12,440 --> 00:21:15,810
Since it's after school now
we thought we should help out a bit.

308
00:21:15,810 --> 00:21:17,230
Unnecessary troubles.

309
00:21:17,230 --> 00:21:19,320
Can we help you out?

310
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:22,450
Of course that would help us out a lot!

311
00:21:23,240 --> 00:21:25,200
{\i1}How cunning...!{\i0}

312
00:21:25,660 --> 00:21:27,950
Then we should split up and get things done.

313
00:21:27,950 --> 00:21:28,910
Yes!

314
00:21:30,040 --> 00:21:32,040
Please do!

315
00:21:35,580 --> 00:21:37,590
{\i1}This must be that delicious thing{\i0}

316
00:21:37,590 --> 00:21:40,920
{\i1}that our uncle sent in congratulations
that Ayumi was talking about!{\i0}

317
00:21:46,850 --> 00:21:49,180
{\i1}They're all Kin-san Ramen?!{\i0}

318
00:21:49,810 --> 00:21:51,680
{\i1}I'll pretend I never saw this.{\i0}

319
00:21:52,060 --> 00:21:54,730
Ayumi can I show you a magic trick?

320
00:21:54,730 --> 00:21:57,650
Oh... that's something I want to see!

321
00:21:57,940 --> 00:22:00,940
Stay there. It will only be an instant.

322
00:22:00,940 --> 00:22:01,780
Yup!

323
00:22:08,280 --> 00:22:12,660
This is amazing!
This is more amazing than the people on TV!

324
00:22:12,660 --> 00:22:13,960
Were you amused by that?

325
00:22:13,960 --> 00:22:14,870
Yup yup yup!

326
00:22:15,460 --> 00:22:18,960
{\i1}Don't use your ability for play!
You've knocked Ayumi out of her wits!{\i0}

327
00:22:19,380 --> 00:22:21,170
If you're going to play 
I'll have you go home!

328
00:22:21,170 --> 00:22:24,840
Yeah yeah... your big brother is scary.

329
00:22:24,840 --> 00:22:27,340
And you're helping us too!

330
00:22:28,930 --> 00:22:31,640
Then we shall excuse ourselves here.

331
00:22:31,640 --> 00:22:35,850
You're going to go home?
I'll make dinner so I'd like you to eat that at least...

332
00:22:35,850 --> 00:22:37,900
We don't have enough dishes for four.

333
00:22:37,900 --> 00:22:39,650
Or so he says.

334
00:22:41,270 --> 00:22:44,440
It's all right. We'll meet again.

335
00:22:45,530 --> 00:22:46,450
Yeah...

336
00:22:52,620 --> 00:22:54,410
Oh Haro-haro.

337
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:56,790
So it is a fad after all.

338
00:22:56,790 --> 00:23:03,210
That's right! Yusa Nishimori
known as Yusarin. She's so cute!

339
00:23:03,760 --> 00:23:07,180
To think something like this sells...
that's the sign of the apocalypse.

340
00:23:09,340 --> 00:23:15,640
Ayu's new school is right next to Big Brother Yu's!
So she wants to go to school together!

341
00:23:15,640 --> 00:23:17,640
They'd think I have a 
sis-com (sister complex).

342
00:23:17,640 --> 00:23:20,270
Sis-com? Is that some kind of a contest?

343
00:23:20,270 --> 00:23:21,400
It isn't.

344
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:26,190
But still Hoshinoumi Academy...
what a wonderful name!

345
00:23:26,650 --> 00:23:31,910
Yeah it's a name that sounds like one
that was made just for you...

346
00:23:37,120 --> 00:23:38,370
Hey.

347
00:23:41,250 --> 00:23:49,130
{\i1}That night I had a dream. I'm sure it was
because of Ayumi's farfetched announcement.{\i0}

348
00:23:52,390 --> 00:23:55,390
{\i1}But who was that?{\i0}
